# Configuration and Secrets

## Secrets policy
- Never hardcode API keys or credentials in source files.
- Use environment variables first for sensitive values.
- If local credential files are used, keep them out of version control.
- Never store full bank account numbers, card numbers, SSNs, or login credentials in any markdown file in this repo. Use rounded amounts, ranges, or last-four-digit references only.

## Configuration policy
- Keep configuration paths simple and documented.
- Use clear names for each configurable option.
- Prefer secure defaults that work for local private use.

## Validation
- Validate required configuration early in a workflow.
- Show user-friendly error messages with fix steps.
- Log technical details separately from user-facing guidance.

## Project-specific policy (Racing ICS Calendar)

- This is a public repo by design (so GitHub Pages can serve calendar feeds for free). That means any secret accidentally committed leaks publicly the moment it's pushed — treat the secrets policy above as load-bearing, not advisory.
- No personal financial identifiers anywhere in the repo (`README.md`, `NOTES.md`, YAML, code, commit messages, branch names). If finance-adjacent context ever needs to be referenced, use rounded values, ranges, or last-four references only.
- No local-machine paths (Windows `C:\Users\...`, macOS `/Users/...`, OneDrive sync paths) in any tracked file. Use repo-relative paths or generic descriptions instead.
- The pre-push privacy checklist in `.cursor/rules/racing-project-context.mdc` is the canonical sign-off list before every push; do not bypass it.
